programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: No Pain No Gain
programme.desc: Once a sun-worshipping fashion model, Linda led a charmed life of good looks. After the devastating loss of her family, life became difficult. Linda is willing to do anything to recover her former looks and finds out that beauty comes with a price.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: The Homecoming Queen Gets Her Crown Back
programme.desc: In her youth, Catherine was a wild child punk rocker whose bright red mohawk got her elected homecoming queen. But now that Catherine is a single mother of twin teenage daughters, she feels like she's lost her young, eye-catching style.
programme.sub-title: The Homecoming Queen Gets Her Crown Back

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Guilty Of Needing A Makeover
programme.desc: After a career as a cop and a private investigator, Lita worked her way through law school while raising her son. She's finished school and taken the bar exam, but her face and body have paid the price.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Prepping For The Big Day
programme.desc: Lilia is the first in her family to finish college. She helps support her family and bought a house she shares with her mother. Her achievements have carried a price; she looks old and tired compared to her friends.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: A New Look On Life
programme.desc: At one time Trisha was a golden locked, free-spirited surfer, but once she settled down and had children her looks and self-esteem took a downward spiral. Suddenly single again, Trisha needs help searching for her energetic youth.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Out of Hiding
programme.desc: Tammy has lost over 100 pounds, but says she feels like she actually looks older! After years of hiding under oversized clothes and bulky glasses, she doesn't know how to dress and take care of her new body.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Debbie Rotchell
programme.desc: Essex girl Debbie Rotchell, 49, smokes 15,000 cigarettes a year and loves to sunbathe. Debbie gets a wake-up call when a poll of one hundred people puts her at 55. Just as well Nicky Hambleton-Jones is on hand with her time-fighting trio.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 6
programme.desc: When Du Plessis instructs the family to be around for dinner, they are intrigued to hear he's planning a big announcement. However, he won't be drawn on details and tells them to be patient.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 7
programme.desc: Alice and Danny are delighted when the Animal Hospital is given responsibility for the rescue and conservation of animals in the region – it's a big achievement after all their hard work.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 8
programme.desc: Danny and Alice are concerned about a missing male giraffe but Du Plessis is confident he can find him. He's as good as his word but they're upset to discover Mara lions have killed the giraffe.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 9
programme.desc: The family frantically dig for Charlotte in the rubble, hoping that somehow she has survived. Rowan arrives and takes charge of the situation, directing them to be more methodical in their rescue efforts.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 10
programme.desc: Danny and Alice are enjoying being together but agree to keep their relationship under wraps for the moment. However, they're unaware Georgina has heard their every word!

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 1
programme.desc: Danny and Alice's project to re-habilitate a group of circus elephants has been a huge success but now they have too many elephants on Leopard's Den, so they urgently need to move the circus herd to the National Park.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 2
programme.desc: Leopard's Den is helping to build a new school in the township but when Danny hurts his back he begins to have a crisis about his age. Danny and Alice are surprised when Vanessa comes to them for advice.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 3
programme.desc: Mara is hosting a beauty pageant and Rowan realises he needs all the publicity he can get. He buys a tiger from a zoo and convinces Alice he plans to rehabilitate it. Alice is enjoying working with her brother and even defends him to Danny.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 2
programme.desc: Professional scuba diver Brian Green has been found floating and not breathing, and is on a boat near the Noises, a group of islands in the Hauraki Gulf. The team has to move fast.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 3
programme.desc: On Great Mercury Island near Coromandel, a scuba diver has surfaced unconscious without a pulse. Without Rescue 1 he may soon be dead.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 4
programme.desc: The Rescue 1 team respond to a call out where an elderly couple in their 60s are in a critical condition after a head on collision.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 3
programme.desc: Tasmania Police is on high alert after a prisoner escapes from jail. The man is armed and dangerous. The Rescue Helicopter is called in to assist with the manhunt. Things turn deadly when they spot him.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 4
programme.desc: Hiker Robert had trained for over 6 months for the remote Cradle Mountain bush walk. With his young daughter in tow they set off on a 48 km walk. Three hours into the walk Roberts health takes a turn for the worse.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 5
programme.desc: A young man has flipped his quad bike and can't move his neck. Later that night, the crew is called to a suburban house because a DIY homebuilder has fallen through the roof in his house – and there's a bone sticking out through his jeans.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 6
programme.desc: De Anna and her husband were celebrating their 50th wedding anniversary on board a luxury liner. The ship's doctor radios for help. But the liner is a long way out at sea. Can the rescue crew get to De Anna in time?

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 1
programme.desc: 14 year-old motor-cross rider, Kacee gets the death wobbles and cartwheels over the top of his handle bars and hits the ground head first. He's now struggling to breath and is barely able to talk. Team Air Rescue needs to get Kacee to the hospital fast.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 5
programme.desc: A truck driver who had one leg amputated 40 years ago, has crashed his truck and crushed his remaining leg. If Rescue 1 can't get him to hospital in time, he will bleed to death.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 6
programme.desc: Westpac chopper paramedic Bruce Kerr has a frantic battle to save a car crash victim with a life-threatening head injury.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 7
programme.desc: Auckland's Westpac helicopter crew races to save a 39 year old forestry worker who has been struck on the head leaving him paralyzed from the waist down.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 8
programme.desc: The chopper crew races to save a woman with a rare disease who's in danger of suffocating from uncontrollable muscle spasms; a badly burnt toddler at Cooks Beach needs an urgent airlift to hospital.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 9
programme.desc: The chopper team is called out to save a pilot who's trapped in the wreck of his hang glider and a diabetic bus driver is found seriously ill after four days lying on his floor.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 2
programme.desc: Fishing buddies Scott, Wayne and Wayne's son Andrew head out to their favorite fishing spot, but when a freak wave hits their boat they have no choice but to SOS for help. Within minutes, the boat capsizes. Can the Air Rescue crew get to them in time?

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 3
programme.desc: 71 year-old retired nurse Sandra was exploring Tasmania's Cradle Mountain when she slipped and fractured her wrist. She's in excruciating pain and night is falling. Visibility is dangerously low. Can the rescue team get in close enough to get them out?

programme.title: Classic Races: Grand Prix Races since 1934
programme.desc: Since 1934 the Grand Prix has been the most exciting and fascinating world championship in the world. With its state-of-the-art vehicles featuring horsepower from the biggest brands, it never fails to wow its viewers.

programme.title: Classic Races: Rallye Year 1972 - A Ford Success Story
programme.desc: The international championship for manufacturers was a rally series which ran from 1970 to 1972. Car manufacturers such as Porsche, Renault and Ford all took part, with Ford having an exceptionally successful year in 1972.
programme.sub-title: Rallye Year 1972 - A Ford Success Story

programme.title: Classic Races: German Touring Championship 1992
programme.desc: The 1992 German Touring Car Championship is one of the most important racing series in German motorsport for sure. It's hard, merciless and well known for its die-hard battles between the ruthless competitors.

programme.title: Classic Races: Touring Car Grand Prix, Argentina 1964
programme.desc: Tropical temperatures, never-ending dust and curves: those are just some of the many difficulties for man and machine during the 1964 Grand Prix in Argentina. This race was responsible for taking the Mercedes brand to the top.

programme.title: Classic Races: Indy 500 1994
programme.desc: The Indy 500 is one of the world's most spectacular motor races in the world. Watched by a huge number of people, this motorsports event doesn't fail to impress at the Indianapolis Motor Speedway.

programme.title: Classic Races: German Rallye Championship 1983
programme.desc: The German rally championship is one of the most popular motorsport series and has been running since 1970. At the 1983 race, the sporty models from Opel saw exceptional success.

programme.title: Classic Races: Quattro The New Dimension 1985
programme.desc: With the introduction of the Group D-Monsters in the World Rally Championships, the fight for the title got harder and harder. Thats why Audi brought a strong trump onto the road in 1985 - The Sport Quattro. And with it began a new dimension.

programme.title: Classic Races: The Rallye World Championship 1982
programme.desc: The African continent is always a difficult terrain for rally drivers. That wasn't any different for the 1982 World Rally Championship, when heat, dust, mud and hardly passable routes posed major challenges for drivers, co-drivers and engines.

programme.title: Classic Races: Mercedes Races Again 1954/55
programme.desc: In 1954, after more than 20 years of abstinence, Mercedes returns to Grand Prix racing. With a lot of engagement, advanced engineering and with the best Grand-Prix-drivers of the world, Mercedes wanted to enjoy success in motorsports again.

programme.title: Classic Ride: Amphicar
programme.desc: The Amphicar 770 is a rare classic. Its special attraction is that you drive motorboat on the road. It may not be the fastest car on the street, but it’s ready to be used on the water as well.

programme.title: Classic Ride: MG TC
programme.desc: The MG TC is a sporty, but also extremely spartan car with technology from the late 1940s. Thus the car might be somewhat susceptible to technical problems, but it’s very easy to maintain.

programme.title: Classic Ride: BMW 319
programme.desc: The BMW 319/1 is one of the rarest and most demanded pre-war classic cars from Germany. Only 178 of them were ever built. Nowadays a well-maintained BMW 319/1 costs more than a Ferrari.

programme.title: Classic Ride: Ron William's Cadillac
programme.desc: The 1952 Cadillac Fleetwood is also known as the American Rolls-Royce, because it’s the car of celebrities, presidents, millionaires and mafia bosses. Only around 16,000 units were built, so it’s a treasured collector’s piece.

programme.title: Tyler Perry's Assisted Living: To Trust Or Not To Trust
programme.desc: Jeremy and Leah have reason to finally be confident about their decision to move. Sandra has a change of heart concerning Lindor, and her parents want to know why. (S1, ep22)
programme.sub-title: To Trust Or Not To Trust

programme.title: Tyler Perry's Assisted Living: A Fight For Honor
programme.desc: Jeremy and Leah are infuriated after learning what Sheriff Luckett has done to Sandra. Mr. Brown takes on the responsibility of preparing dinner for the kids. (S1, ep23)

programme.title: Tyler Perry's Assisted Living: A Dangerous Situation
programme.desc: Cora tries to convince Mr. Brown to pitch in and help get Jeremy out of jail. Jeremy and Leah have a conversation with Sandra about invading her privacy. (S1, ep24)

programme.title: Tyler Perry's Assisted Living: The Dirty Denial
programme.desc: Vinny is in an unusually good mood and causes everyone concern. Plans to open the living facility come to a halt when Vinny receives disturbing news. (S1, ep25)

programme.title: Tyler Perry's House of Payne: Someone
programme.desc: Miranda's interested in giving Calvin a second chance. After his divorce, Calvin decides to date again. Miranda and Calvin's new woman know each other.

programme.title: Tyler Perry's House of Payne: Something's Rotten
programme.desc: Calvin and Miranda's divorce drama grows. Jazmine gets candid with Ella about wanting to have sex for the first time. Calvin doesn't want anybody talking to Miranda, including Ella.

programme.title: Tyler Perry's House of Payne: Hard Lessons
programme.desc: Curtis upsets Ella and must change his tune. Calvin confronts Miranda about talking to Laura. Miranda tells Calvin how she feels.

programme.title: Tyler Perry's House of Payne: Lucky Cards
programme.desc: Ella warns Curtis not to revive his old gambling habits. Miranda and Laura seek advice from Ella. Miranda walks in on Laura and Calvin.

programme.title: Being Mary Jane: Facing Fears
programme.desc: When Mary Jane is rushed to the hospital after her accident the family rallies around her. Paul Sr. handles David, and Helen unburdens them of Lisa while Kara fights for Mary Jane at SNC. (S3, ep1)

programme.title: Being Mary Jane: Louie Louie
programme.desc: Stuck in the house with nothing else to do, a new set of problems arise for Mary Jane when Cece reveals her plans to extort her. Meanwhile, SNC hires Marisol, a new, young replacement. (S3, ep2)

programme.title: Being Mary Jane: Sparrow
programme.desc: When Mary Jane gets the devastating news of the death of a loved one, she'll be forced to confront her life choices, deal with her family and face David. (S3, ep3)

programme.title: Paranormal State: Desperate Households
programme.desc: When Julie and her family moved into their dream home in suburban New Jersey they quickly realized they were not alone.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Haunted Connection
programme.desc: P.R.S. is called in to help a young mother tormented by an otherworldly connection to a teenage girl murdered in her neighborhood years ago. Could she have psychic ability or is there a more sinister force at work?

programme.title: Paranormal State: Church of the Damned
programme.desc: Jason and his family can no longer do renovations of an abandoned Kansas church, especially after they found their father in the basement crying and frightened because of the menacing activity.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Who Is the Lurking Man?
programme.desc: PRS travels to Newcastle, CA to investigate a house with paranormal forces so strong, the family has cleared out. Ryan believes the Native American land may hold the key to the mystery and leads the team in a fight to reclaim a scared family's house.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Suicide Possession
programme.desc: Joan and her boyfriend Tony are seeing apparitions in their New Jersey home. Both are concerned that the spirits are influencing their behavior: a non-drinker, Tony has turned to the bottle while Joan has thoughts of harming herself.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Hostage to Fear
programme.desc: P.R.S. is summoned to help a family who has been haunted for years by spirits lurking in the house. Upon arrival the team finds a family that has become prisoners in their own home.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Man of the House
programme.desc: PRS is called to help a grandmother and her frightened grandson when renovations on her 19th century house stir up the pipe-smoking specter of a former tenant named Alfred.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Bedroom Eyes
programme.desc: PRS travels to rural Pennsylvania to investigate a haunting that began after a new couple moved into an old family farm.?Over the next three days, hidden tragedies are uncovered and latent psychic abilities are revealed.

programme.title: Paranormal State: School House Haunting
programme.desc: PRS travels to Massachusetts to investigate an old schoolhouse where children's voices disturb a couple who've made it their home.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Laws of Attraction
programme.desc: When Paula's young autistic son Michael, with limited verbal skills uttered the words "Go away scary dead boy" -- it sent a chill up her spine.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Lost Souls
programme.desc: PRS and Psychic/medium Michelle Belanger investigate a Pennsylvania home; where a mother named Kathy and her son Michael have both felt the presence of a young boy and hear voices calling, "Mom?" but no one is there.

programme.title: Paranormal State: The Firehouse
programme.desc: Everyone from the chief to the trainees at the Clementon Fire Department is convinced that the ghost of a former member is haunting their firehouse.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Devil in Jersey
programme.desc: PRS delves deep into the pine barrens of the Garden State to separate myth from reality about the so-called "Jersey Devil." Accompanied by a cryptozoologist the team interviews eye witnesses and experts in search of the truth.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Paranormal Intervention
programme.desc: Carol Ann stays awake every night taping the voices of the dead. PRS cuts their winter break short to help her curtail her obsession and close this doorway to the dead--for good.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Wookey Hole
programme.desc: The team visits Wookey Hole, where legend has it a witch once turned to stone. Clashing cymbals and ancient pagan rituals await as the team explores spectacular caves said to lead to the underworld.

programme.title: Most Haunted: The Stanley Hotel
programme.desc: The twelfth season brings the team to the USA where they investigate famously haunted locations. They start with the Stanley Hotel, the inspiration for Stephen King's horror classic "The Shining."

programme.title: Most Haunted: Waverly Hills
programme.desc: Thought to be one of the most haunted locations in North America, the Waverly Hills Sanatorium in Kentucky is truly a horrific location. The team were pushed to their limits at this derelict hospital.

programme.title: Most Haunted: West Virginia State Penitentiary
programme.desc: Until 1995, the West Virginia Penitentiary held some gruesome inmates. The team investigates claims that some of its most violent inmates have hung around to terrorize anyone who enters their world.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Sleepy Hollow
programme.desc: One cannot say the words "Sleepy Hollow" without invoking the famous story of the Headless Horseman. The team heads down to the cemetery and sets up camp at the location of the infamous wooden bridge.

programme.title: Most Haunted: New London Ledge Lighthouse
programme.desc: The New London Ledge Lighthouse in Connecticut sets the investigation team adrift as it isolates them for an entire night of investigation. Will they meet the lighthouse's infamous ghost, Ernie?

programme.title: Most Haunted: Fort Delaware
programme.desc: Fort Delaware is a huge and imposing location that once held 13,000 prisoners. With such a large area to go over, the team has their work cut out investigating the fort before sunrise.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: Merry Christmas from Grandpa
programme.desc: On Christmas Eve, Jonathan shows three men what will happen in the future if the Earth continues to be ravaged by pollution. One of the men is an energy official another is a farmer and the third one is the President.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: Pilot - Part 1
programme.desc: In the series opener, we meet Jonathan Smith, a probationary angel who has been sent to help people on Earth. He befriends residents at a retirement home. The administrator at the home has a brother named Mark who is suspicious of Jonathan.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: Pilot - Part 2
programme.desc: Jonathan helps the residents of Havencrest, when they learn that the retirement home is going to be sold. Jonathan must reveal his real identity to Mark in order to complete the assignment.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: To Touch The Moon
programme.desc: Jonathan helps a terminally ill boy and his mother. Meanwhile, Mark deals with a thief abandoned by his folks.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: Return of the Masked Rider
programme.desc: Jonathan and Mark help aging movie heroes to stand up to a street gang known as Satan's Helpers. They persuade a young boxer not to throw a big fight when the gang tries to bully him.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: Song of the Wild West
programme.desc: Jonathan and Mark assist a young country singer who is hoping to follow in her mother's footsteps. Next, they help a widow mourning her late husband.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: One Fresh Batch of Lemonade - Part 1
programme.desc: Jonathan must find a way to help Deke, a college football star whose dreams of reaching the pros are shattered by a tragic motorcycle accident.
programme.sub-title: One Fresh Batch of Lemonade - Part 1

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Debbie Rotchell
programme.desc: Essex girl Debbie Rotchell, 49, smokes 15,000 cigarettes a year and loves to sunbathe. Debbie gets a wake-up call when a poll of one hundred people puts her at 55. Just as well Nicky Hambleton-Jones is on hand with her time-fighting trio.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Military Makeover
programme.desc: As former Marine, Kimberly wasn't "trained" in the art of looking feminine and as a single mother of three, now isn't the time for her to begin learning. She just doesn't have the time. Time to make Kimberly look 10 Years Younger!

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Hairy Mary Quite Contrary
programme.desc: Mary is an overworked telecommuter and mother of twin 5-year-old girls. Since she works from home, Mary has traded in her business suits for sweats and a ponytail. We'll see if we can make Mary look 10 Years Younger.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Better Days Ahead
programme.desc: Serena came to the U.S. from Cambodia at age seven and helped care for her younger siblings. She loves them, but does not love being mistaken for their mother. Serena had to grow up too fast, but she doesn't have to look like it.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: From Rosy Red To Peaches And Cream
programme.desc: Monica is a working mother of three whose rosacea has gotten worse with every passing year and she is tired of hearing, 'Oh, you've been out in the sun?' The team injects motivation back into Monica's life and look.
programme.sub-title: From Rosy Red To Peaches And Cream

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Faith in a New Look
programme.desc: Peggy is a single chaplain who uses her faith and people skills helping sick children in a children's hospital. She wants to regain her confidence with a younger, sassier look – that's where we come in. It's time to make Peggy look 10 Years Younger!

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: From Backstage To Center Stage
programme.desc: Mimi was a successful touring backup singer, and decided to take a final bow after getting married and having her daughter. Now that her daughter is older, she is ready to jump back on stage and needs the look to match.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: From Bummed Out To Belle Of The Ball
programme.desc: Jennifer has been feeling older since her back injury six months ago. Her job requires shopping in Beverly Hills and attending charity balls in appropriate attire. But at six feet tall, size 16 and on a budget, this is no easy task. She needs a makeover!
programme.sub-title: From Bummed Out To Belle Of The Ball

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Saying "I Do" To A New Look
programme.desc: Driving a big rig over two million miles and being a single dad have taken a huge toll on Michael's appearance. But major dental prosthetics and state-of-the-art dermatology bring out his softer side, then it's up to the Glam Squad to find a new look!
programme.sub-title: Saying "I Do" To A New Look

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Tony Goodwin "One Year On"
programme.desc: We revisit Midlands' band promoter Tony Goodwin who's poll of one hundred people last year suggested he was a colossal thirteen years older than he actually was.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Mom's Day Out
programme.desc: Nancy is a mother who's almost out of gas and in need of a rejuvenating jump-start. The glam squad breathes life into Nancy's fashion sense and provides this over-worked parent some relief from her frazzled life.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Jayne English
programme.desc: Can Nicky Hambleton-Jones and her illustrious team of experts turn back time for 41-year-old Jayne English who went from a size 22 to a size 10 in just 18 months?

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Nerys McGarry
programme.desc: Can the team pull off their biggest challenge to date and make Nerys McGarry - who has lost eight stone - 21 years younger?

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 3
programme.desc: Mara is hosting a beauty pageant and Rowan realises he needs all the publicity he can get. He buys a tiger from a zoo and convinces Alice he plans to rehabilitate it. Alice is enjoying working with her brother and even defends him to Danny.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 4
programme.desc: Danny and Alice have been preparing a cheetah for release in the wild but for some reason Danny's mind isn't on the job. He's been pre-occupied because he plans to buy a ring and propose to Alice!

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 5
programme.desc: Danny and Alice are taking a well deserved holiday but Olivia's upset to learn they're leaving that day. Angry at missing out on a driving lesson, she decides to take the jeep out on her own.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 6
programme.desc: Alice is enjoying her new job at Mara even though her animal census has revealed they have a lone male hyena that needs a pack. Du Plessis isn't happy about Alice working for next door.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 7
programme.desc: Danny's continued estrangement from Alice is really starting to take its toll. Over at Mara, Alice puts on a brave face as she meets Tom Cox, the owner of a rare male black leopard.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 8
programme.desc: Caroline returns to find that all is not well at Leopard's Den. Danny has been putting a brave face on his ban but his attempts at helping out around the house are getting on everyone's nerves and Alice is finding his back-seat vetting especially hard.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 9
programme.desc: Danny is delighted to have his veterinary license back again and being back at work is helping to distract him from the impending anniversary of Sarah's death.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 10
programme.desc: Du Plessis is restless after his heart surgery but the family insist he needs to relax. Meanwhile Danny and Alice are happy to have closed down a zoo down that has been mistreating animals.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 3
programme.desc: 71 year-old retired nurse Sandra was exploring Tasmania's Cradle Mountain when she slipped and fractured her wrist. She's in excruciating pain and night is falling. Visibility is dangerously low. Can the rescue team get in close enough to get them out?

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 4
programme.desc: Mountain bike fanatic, Blake was out riding when he clipped a tree and crashed into a rock. It's a time critical rescue mission. And what the rescue crew doesn't yet know is that Blake is about to take a turn for the worse.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 5
programme.desc: Motorbike rider, Lachlan was testing out his newly designed dirt-bike track when he lost control on a jump. His femur has been badly shattered. The Air Rescue crew is tasked with flying Lachlan to hospital but his medical dramas have only just begun.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 6
programme.desc: Retirees Diane and husband Gary were just a few hours into their Pacific Island cruise of a lifetime when disaster struck. Diane toppled down a set of stairs and now she's in need of urgent medical attention.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 10
programme.desc: The Rescue 1 team are en route to the scene of a horrific accident. A pedestrian has been hit by a truck and is in a critical condition.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 11
programme.desc: A woman is badly hurt after being knocked down a bank by her pet goat, a man is found with serious injuries on a remote beach, and 11-year old girl has fallen down a bank and suffered suspected spinal damage.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 12
programme.desc: The chopper team is called out to save a motorbike racer who's crashed at 200ks per hour and a woman scalded by an exploding radiator, plus an elderly golfer in a kilt suffers a heart attack on the 18th hole.

programme.title: The Embassy: Episode 2
programme.desc: Retired Army Officer, Ben arrives at the Embassy in tears. His young Thai wife has suddenly gone missing. Rodney has been having way too much of a good time in Vietnam. He's overstayed his visa and run up a $1,500 hotel bill.

programme.title: The Embassy: Episode 3
programme.desc: Music journalist, Illario the Lothario, is one of many foreign revelers who have come unstuck. His passport is drenched and no longer valid. He arrives to the Embassy, only to fall head over heals for a dashing Thai diplomat.

programme.title: The Embassy: Episode 4
programme.desc: Best mates Rhys and Benny, are on their first-ever overseas holiday together. They're staying in the heart of Phuket and the sky's the limit. They've done everything their parents warned them not to.

programme.title: My Big Fat Fetish
programme.desc: Most of us are trying to lose weight but this is a film about a group of big women who are happy with their larger size and some of whom want to get even fatter.

programme.title: Classic Ride: Ron William's Cadillac
programme.desc: The 1952 Cadillac Fleetwood is also known as the American Rolls-Royce, because it’s the car of celebrities, presidents, millionaires and mafia bosses. Only around 16,000 units were built, so it’s a treasured collector’s piece.

programme.title: Classic Ride: Jaguar E-Type
programme.desc: A legend celebrates its 50th anniversary. In 1961 The Jaguar E-Type was shown for the first time on the Motor Show Geneva.

programme.title: Classic Ride: Mercedes 300 SL Gullwing
programme.desc: The Mercedes 300SL might be the most exciting sports car of the post-war era. A panel of judges even named it the sports car of the century. Hans Kleissl from Polling near Munich owns one of the world's leading repair and restoration shops.

programme.title: Classic Ride: Porsche Carrera RS
programme.desc: In the early 70s it was the fastest and most sportive production sports car in Germany: the Porsche Carrera RS. Today the RS is a classic Porsche with the highest acclaim.

programme.title: Classic Ride: Ron Williams and his Cougar
programme.desc: After the sensational success of the 1964 presented Ford Mustang, the Ford Motor Company decided to build another exciting car, based on the Mustang, the Mercury Cougar.

programme.title: Classic Ride: DeLorean
programme.desc: It is one of the most spectacular cars of the last 30 years: the Delorean DMC-12. But after 9000 built cars, the production came to an end in 1982.

programme.title: Classic Ride: Melkus
programme.desc: Revisiting the past to portray the classic and veteran cars of decades gone by, meeting the personalities who wrote automotive history, sending very old cars running round very fast circuits.

programme.title: Classic Ride: Audi S1 Quattro, Part 1
programme.desc: It's the most powerful and most spectacular rally car ever built: The Audi Sport quattro S1. Based on the regular Audi Sport Quattro, the S1 is 32 cm shorter, has giant wings and spreads anxiety, fear and excitement among rally drivers and fans.

programme.title: Classic Ride: Audi S1 Quattro, Part 2
programme.desc: It is sexy, spectacular and comes with tremendous speed: the Audi Sport quattro S1, the most exciting rally car ever built. In part 2 of the S1 special, Classic Rides accompanies S1 pilot Michael Gerber during the second day of the Rally Legend.

programme.title: Classic Ride: Alfa Romeo
programme.desc: Alfa Romeo, even nowadays the paragon of design, Italian car making and car racing. But from the official racing Alfa Romeo departed long ago.

programme.title: Go Green: Opel Ampera
programme.desc: The Opel Ampera is the first electric family saloon that is designed to convince anyone that¿s wary of electric cars. After its introduction at the 2011 Geneva Motor Show, the mid-range car is now available for sale.

programme.title: Go Green: Green, Greener, Greenest
programme.desc: Green, greener, greenest ... the market for alternative power sources just keeps growing, and that won't stop. Practically every automobile manufacturer has developed an electric car or a hybrid model vehicle.

programme.title: Go Green: International Motor Show Frankfurt
programme.desc: The market for alternative drive technologies just keeps growing and the best place to present the newest cars is at the biggest car show in the world, - the IAA, in Frankfurt, Germany.

programme.title: Go Green: Volvo C30
programme.desc: The Volvo C30 electric is a purely electric car without combustion engine or range extender. Since 2010 the Swedish company works on their concept to realize pure electric driving.

programme.title: Go Green: Lexus RX 450 h
programme.desc: The Lexus RX 450h is the second revised hybrid model coming from the Toyota Group. Go Green checks out the full hybrid SUV. Plus: The young car manufactory Artega emphasizes the importance of ecologically sensitive sports cars.

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Second Chances
programme.desc: A Taelon program offers a transformation into a younger, healthier version of oneself. Liam fears that something more dangerous is also happening. Lili is worried that Doors' run for the presidency is negatively affecting the resistance.

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Payback
programme.desc: A mysterious death by poisoning creates questions about the safety of portal technology. When a Taelon is killed in the same manner, the investigation leads to a very smart scientist that even the Resistance was scared to work with.

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Friendly Fire
programme.desc: Paul Chandler plots an attack on the Taelon Embassy in DC with the ship he stole from Lili. He begs her to join him in beginning an all out war.

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Volunteers

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Bliss

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Heroes and Heartbreak
programme.desc: Augur is recruited by a Taelon weapons project, but the others are worried about his involvement. When the project is launched earlier than originally planned to fight a Jiridian fleet, the Earth is in danger.

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Message in a Bottle
programme.desc: A Jiridian probe headed for Earth is shot down by the Taelon Embassy and crashes outside of D.C. Liam recovers the probe, but he, Augur, and Julia are captured by another underground resistance movement led by the real Colonel Liam Kincaid.

programme.desc: Bugs have been a part of David’s daily diet for over twelve years, watch as he braces himself to eat his most venomous bug yet. Kelly’s daily diet consists of food solely gathered from the dumpster.

programme.title: Buying Alaska: Living Off The Land
programme.desc: Ryan and Skippy want to be able to get everything they need to live from their own land. And after buying a series of homes with major problems, they want this home to be their own piece of Alaska.

programme.title: Buying Alaska: The Wilderness Man
programme.desc: Bud Jacque is looking for his Alaskan wilderness home with his wife, Susan. He's a man of simple tastes; all he wants is a great view, and somewhere to hunt and fish. She might want a little more.

programme.title: Buying Alaska: Sled Dogs
programme.desc: Andy and Carolyn are avid dogsledders. They are moving to Alaska in hopes of becoming champion dog mushers. But to do that, they first need to find a home where they can train their team.

programme.title: Buying Alaska: Kenai River Cabins
programme.desc: Scott and Kelly are Alaskan born-and-bred and true lovers of the outdoors with a passion for fishing. All Scott wants is a place on the Kenai River, so that he can fish right from his backyard.

programme.title: Buying Alaska: Bear Necessities
programme.desc: Mike York and his son Hunter live on Alaska's wildest island, Kodiak! Best friends and hunting partners, they are looking for a remote recreational property to hunt.

programme.title: Buying Alaska: The Ultimate Alaskan Island
programme.desc: Former Broncos kicker Jason Elam and his wife Tammy have moved to Alaska for their post-NFL lives. They're looking for the ultimate secluded home - their own private island, in Sitka, Alaska.

programme.title: Buying Alaska: Flying Home
programme.desc: Jackson Meyer is a licensed pilot in Soldotna, Alaska. He and his wife, Kandi, are looking for a remote cabin for their family in Seldovia that they can fly to every chance they get.

programme.title: Buying Alaska: Moose Mount Cabins
programme.desc: Ernie came to Alaska over twenty years ago to hunt, and he's passed that love of hunting to his wife and kids. They have a cabin with no running water and electricity, but they want an upgrade.

programme.title: Buying Alaska: Alaska Man Caves
programme.desc: Dan Miotke, a fireman living with his wife and two daughters in Homer, Alaska, is taking the idea of a man cave to a new level, looking for a cheap property that he can fix up into his own man cabin.

programme.title: Buying Alaska: Winter Wanderland
programme.desc: Jason and Alana want a home built for the harsh snows of the Mat-Su Valley. Will they take a hunting cabin filled with animal heads, one crafted for the Alaskan sun, or one needing rehab?

programme.title: Buying Alaska: Hooked On A Lake
programme.desc: Life on an Alaskan lake is what Steve and Peg want, in the wilderness of the Mat-Su Valley - a secluded place where, even in the long, harsh Alaskan winters, fish teem beneath the frozen ice.

programme.title: Buying Alaska: Snow Machines & Bear Attacks
programme.desc: Newlyweds Garret and Noelle want a remote home in the Alaskan wilderness that’s so off-the-grid, there’s no road leading to it. In the winter, they’ll have to travel by snowmobile.

programme.title: Buying Alaska: Ruff-Ing It
programme.desc: Pete and Anja want to buy an Alaskan home that’s right for them AND their 21 dogs. They care more about making their Alaskan Huskies comfortable than they do about themselves.

programme.title: Buying Alaska: Baby On Board
programme.desc: Matt and Jessica have a new baby. They want to move into a new home near the ocean around Juneau, Alaska. But waterfront homes are too expensive, so they choose a liveaboard boat!

programme.title: Buying Alaska: Isolated Village
